<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ufendrylistalindir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fendryl Istalindir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/25/02 1:59:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11637.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New ST Keys Source?</span><hr size=1> Upping spawn times doesn't really do much to solve the problem of competition, all it does is push the competition to something further 'up' the chain.  The problem is that the content is shared, if the Statue popped every 10 minutes, that still wouldn't prevent guild_00 from killing it every 10 mins &amp; keeping guild_01 from ever getting a shot.  Sure eventually guild_00 would move on, and guild_01 would get a shot - but they'd only be butting heads at Tormax, or AoW next.<br>
<br>
The real solution is giving every guild the ability to spawn their own content once a week.  That allows everyone the opportunity to progress &amp; do encounters at their own pace &amp; on their own schedule.  Item entry rates don't matter because one groups success doesn't hold back another group now.  Now Guild_00 can do the statue every week (at the intended spawn rate), and Guild_01 can do it whenever they want to as well - and they don't butt heads, but still share the same experience, free of trainings, ooc smacktalk, neckbreathing, tick-tocking, etc.<br>
<br>
